flawed_nl_solution:
Susie earned $10 x 3 = $<<10*3=30>>30 per day.
Last week, she earned a total of $30 x 7 = $<<30*7=210>>210.
She spent $210 x 3/10 = $<<210*3/10=36>>36 on make-up.
While she spent $210 x 2/5 = $<<210*2/5=84>>84 on her skincare products.
Thus, she spent a total of $36 + $84 = $<<36+84=120>>120 from her earnings.
Therefore, Susie is left with $210 - $120 = $<<210-120=90>>90 from her earnings last week.
